modules.description: This module handles IP geolocation lookups and credit checks via a web service API. It works with IP addresses and JSON responses, using a configuration record that includes an API key, package type, and SSL setting. Concrete use cases include retrieving geolocation data for a given IP and checking remaining API credits.

This module provides functions to open and query an IP geolocation database file, retrieving detailed location and network information for IPv4 and IPv6 addresses. It works with metadata and IP records, including country, city, ISP, coordinates, and additional network attributes. Concrete use cases include geolocation-based analytics, IP lookup services, and network diagnostics.

This module provides functions to perform IP geolocation lookups using either a local database file or a web service API. It supports querying detailed location and network information for IPv4 and IPv6 addresses, including country, city, ISP, and coordinates. Concrete use cases include implementing IP-based access control, geolocation analytics, and network troubleshooting tools.
